WEBVTT

00:00:14.500 --> 00:00:16.250
"Suguha's Room"

00:00:18.875 --> 00:00:22.583
<i>"I want to see</i>
<i>virtual reality for myself."</i>

00:00:22.583 --> 00:00:25.833
<i>When was it that I first thought that?</i>

00:00:29.750 --> 00:00:33.042
<i>At first, I saw virtual-reality games</i>

00:00:33.042 --> 00:00:37.208
<i>only as hateful things</i>
<i>that took my brother away.</i>

00:00:37.708 --> 00:00:44.250
<i>But I wanted to see the world my brother loved</i>
<i>with my own eyes, no matter what.</i>

00:00:44.750 --> 00:00:46.750
<i>I wanted to know.</i>

00:00:52.917 --> 00:00:58.542
<i>And I was surprised how enchanted</i>
<i>I became with ALfheim Online.</i>

00:01:01.125 --> 00:01:05.167
<i>The joy of flying through the sky</i>
<i>with your own wings.</i>

00:01:05.750 --> 00:01:10.750
<i>If I could keep flying as far</i>
<i>and as high as my heart desired,</i>

00:01:10.750 --> 00:01:13.875
<i>I'd be willing to give up anything.</i>

00:01:15.833 --> 00:01:17.917
<i>I think I understand now.</i>

00:01:18.417 --> 00:01:22.042
<i>The reason my brother</i>
<i>was so captivated by this world.</i>

00:01:23.583 --> 00:01:28.958
<i>The feelings I've hidden</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:01:28.958 --> 00:01:34.458
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:01:44.708 --> 00:01:55.000
<i>Seeking only a miracle, I wander</i>
<i>through an endless darkness</i>

00:01:55.125 --> 00:02:05.750
<i>If I stay here, I won't</i>
<i>ever see the future again</i>

00:02:05.917 --> 00:02:11.125
<i>Tonight the moon summons me again.</i>
<i>Though I still cannot speak,</i>

00:02:11.125 --> 00:02:14.917
<i>I keep crying out in my heart</i>

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:21.292
<i>My hidden feelings</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:02:21.375 --> 00:02:26.333
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:02:26.458 --> 00:02:32.000
<i>If I can stay stronger a bit longer,</i>

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:38.167
<i>I will go beyond</i>
<i>this sky right in front of me</i>

00:02:40.042 --> 00:02:46.625
<i>I will reach out towards</i>
<i>the future ahead of me</i>

00:02:52.083 --> 00:02:56.083
"To the World Tree"

00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:06.208
Leafa!

00:03:08.417 --> 00:03:12.250
I told you not to call me that
at school, Nagata.

00:03:12.250 --> 00:03:14.875
S-Sorry, Suguha...

00:03:14.958 --> 00:03:18.792
--Why you...
--I-I-I'm sorry! Miss Kirigaya!

00:03:19.292 --> 00:03:23.667
Need something? And you got
early admission into high school,

00:03:23.667 --> 00:03:27.583
so why are you at school?
You're not required to attend.

00:03:27.583 --> 00:03:28.750
Sugu...

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:33.708
I needed to talk to you, Miss Kirigaya,
so I've been waiting since morning.

00:03:33.708 --> 00:03:36.083
You got admitted early too.

00:03:36.083 --> 00:03:41.625
The kendo club adviser asked me
to come in. So, what did you need?

00:03:42.167 --> 00:03:46.625
Sigurd and the others will be
hunting again this afternoon.

00:03:46.625 --> 00:03:50.458
Sorry, I won't be
joining them for a while.

00:03:50.958 --> 00:03:54.708
--Why not?
--I'm heading to Arun.

00:03:54.708 --> 00:03:58.417
Arun? At the base of the World Tree?

00:03:58.417 --> 00:04:02.792
D-Don't tell me you're going
with that Spriggan from yesterday...

00:04:02.792 --> 00:04:06.833
Yeah... I guess so.
I'm going to show him the way.

00:04:06.833 --> 00:04:09.875
Wh-What are you thinking, Leaf--

00:04:12.500 --> 00:04:18.042
Miss Kirigaya. You'll be going so far,
overnight, with a shady guy like that?

00:04:18.583 --> 00:04:21.292
Don't get any weird ideas!

00:04:23.542 --> 00:04:28.542
Anyway, that's how it is.
Give Sigurd and the others my regards.

00:04:29.083 --> 00:04:30.167
Bye!

00:04:30.708 --> 00:04:32.542
"Suguha's Room"

00:04:41.083 --> 00:04:43.625
I'm just showing him the way.

00:04:43.625 --> 00:04:45.125
That's all.

00:05:05.958 --> 00:05:07.708
Link start!

00:05:11.917 --> 00:05:15.833
"Sylvain, Sylph Territory
January 21, 2025"

00:05:25.208 --> 00:05:27.375
Hey, you're early.

00:05:27.375 --> 00:05:31.333
No, I just got here.
I was out shopping.

00:05:31.333 --> 00:05:38.125
Oh, right. I need to get ready too...
This one probably won't be too reliable.

00:05:38.500 --> 00:05:39.542
Yeah.

00:05:39.542 --> 00:05:44.625
Then let's go to the weapons shop.
How much money do you have?

00:05:44.750 --> 00:05:49.167
Um... Is this "Yuld" stuff money?

00:05:49.167 --> 00:05:50.292
Yeah.

00:05:52.958 --> 00:05:55.875
H-Hey. We're leaving, Yui.

00:05:56.750 --> 00:05:58.208
Okay.

00:06:21.875 --> 00:06:25.792
--Why are we going to the tower?
--When flying long distances,

00:06:25.792 --> 00:06:30.750
you start from the top of the tower.
It gives you extra altitude.

00:06:30.750 --> 00:06:31.917
I see.

00:06:31.917 --> 00:06:35.000
You're kidding me!

00:06:38.292 --> 00:06:43.417
Come on, let's get going. I want
to make it through the forest by night.

00:06:48.167 --> 00:06:49.917
This way, this way!

00:06:54.333 --> 00:06:55.375
Leafa!

00:06:57.792 --> 00:06:59.292
Hello, Sigurd.

00:06:59.667 --> 00:07:02.625
You're leaving the party, Leafa?

00:07:02.917 --> 00:07:05.083
Yeah, I guess so.

00:07:05.083 --> 00:07:09.417
Don't you think that will
inconvenience the other members?

00:07:09.417 --> 00:07:15.292
You promised I could join only when I
had time and leave whenever I wanted.

00:07:15.292 --> 00:07:19.958
But you're already
a well-known member of our party.

00:07:19.958 --> 00:07:24.333
If you leave without a reason,
it will damage our reputation.

00:07:29.625 --> 00:07:32.500
Your party members aren't items.

00:07:34.042 --> 00:07:35.542
What was that?

00:07:38.917 --> 00:07:42.833
You can't keep other players
equipped all the time,

00:07:42.833 --> 00:07:46.250
as if they were
your armor or sword.

00:07:46.542 --> 00:07:47.833
You...

00:07:48.542 --> 00:07:52.083
Don't get cocky,
you bottom-feeding Spriggan!

00:07:52.083 --> 00:07:55.208
You're probably an exiled renegade!

00:07:55.208 --> 00:07:59.625
Don't be rude.
Kirito is my new partner!

00:07:59.875 --> 00:08:01.208
What?

00:08:01.208 --> 00:08:06.250
Leafa! Are you abandoning your territory
and becoming a renegade too?

00:08:06.708 --> 00:08:10.167
Yes, I am.
I'm leaving this place.

00:08:11.750 --> 00:08:15.542
I wasn't concerned
if you just buzzed around.

00:08:15.542 --> 00:08:18.833
But acting like a thief is different.

00:08:18.833 --> 00:08:22.125
If you're in another races' territory,

00:08:22.125 --> 00:08:25.500
you can't complain
if you get killed, right?

00:08:32.083 --> 00:08:34.333
This isn't the time, Sigurd.

00:08:34.333 --> 00:08:39.083
If we kill someone who can't fight back
in front of all these people...

00:08:47.542 --> 00:08:51.750
Once you're outside,
you'd better run and hide, Leafa.

00:08:51.750 --> 00:08:57.250
If you betray me now,
you'll surely regret it before long.

00:09:04.625 --> 00:09:07.875
Sorry for involving you in that.

00:09:07.875 --> 00:09:13.042
It's fine... But are you sure about this?
Abandoning your territory...

00:09:16.375 --> 00:09:18.000
H-Hey...

00:09:24.458 --> 00:09:26.917
This is an amazing view.

00:09:26.917 --> 00:09:30.667
The sky's so close.
Like my hand can touch it.

00:09:30.667 --> 00:09:36.125
Isn't it? Whenever I see this sky,
it makes everything else feel small.

00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:45.625
This was a good opportunity.
I always meant to leave this place.

00:09:45.625 --> 00:09:50.917
I see. But it feels like I made
you leave on bad terms.

00:09:50.917 --> 00:09:54.917
Either way, I couldn't have left
on amicable terms.

00:09:55.667 --> 00:09:58.500
Hey, what's a renegade?

00:09:58.500 --> 00:10:04.958
Players who abandon their territories
are renegades. They're looked down on.

00:10:05.667 --> 00:10:09.708
--Are you sure about this?
--Yeah. It's not a problem...

00:10:09.917 --> 00:10:14.792
But why do they want to tie
each other down like that?

00:10:14.792 --> 00:10:17.458
When we all have wings...

00:10:20.667 --> 00:10:23.167
Humans are complex.

00:10:23.708 --> 00:10:25.458
I can't understand
the mentality that causes

00:10:25.458 --> 00:10:29.375
the desire to seek others
to be expressed so oddly.

00:10:29.375 --> 00:10:30.792
Seek others?

00:10:30.792 --> 00:10:32.792
If it were me...

00:10:33.458 --> 00:10:37.042
I'd do this. It's simple
and unmistakable.

00:10:37.042 --> 00:10:42.500
Th-That's an amazing AI.
Are all private pixies like that?

00:10:42.625 --> 00:10:45.333
She's weirder than most...

00:10:46.708 --> 00:10:49.083
O-Oh, I see.

00:10:49.083 --> 00:10:52.167
The desire to seek others...

00:10:52.833 --> 00:10:54.458
Leafa!

00:10:55.167 --> 00:10:58.167
--Oh, Recon.
--I don't believe you!

00:10:59.042 --> 00:11:01.917
Say something before you leave!

00:11:01.917 --> 00:11:04.667
Sorry, I forgot.

00:11:05.333 --> 00:11:09.000
Leafa, is it true you quit the party?

00:11:09.000 --> 00:11:13.458
It was halfway on the spur of the moment.
What are you gonna do?

00:11:13.458 --> 00:11:18.667
Do you even need to ask?
My sword belongs to you alone!

00:11:19.208 --> 00:11:22.208
I don't really need it, though.

00:11:22.208 --> 00:11:27.042
W-Well, that's how it is. So I'll
be going with you, of course.

00:11:27.042 --> 00:11:30.833
Or at least I'd like to.
But something's bothering me.

00:11:30.833 --> 00:11:32.083
What?

00:11:32.083 --> 00:11:36.083
I can't prove anything yet,
but I want to investigate a bit,

00:11:36.083 --> 00:11:39.833
so I'm going to stay in
Sigurd's party a little longer.

00:11:39.833 --> 00:11:41.375
Kirito.

00:11:41.375 --> 00:11:46.083
She has a habit of diving
into trouble, so be careful.

00:11:46.083 --> 00:11:48.500
Y-Yeah, got it.

00:11:48.500 --> 00:11:52.458
And just so we're clear, she's my--

00:11:54.750 --> 00:12:00.375
I think we'll be in the neutral zone awhile.
Send a message if you need anything.

00:12:01.667 --> 00:12:03.125
Ow...

00:12:10.333 --> 00:12:13.083
You said he's a friend from real life?

00:12:13.083 --> 00:12:14.708
More or less.

00:12:15.917 --> 00:12:18.250
What was up with that?

00:12:18.250 --> 00:12:21.000
Nothing, I just think it's nice.

00:12:22.542 --> 00:12:28.292
I can understand his feelings.
He likes you, doesn't he, Leafa?

00:12:28.292 --> 00:12:31.125
How do you feel about him?

00:12:31.542 --> 00:12:33.625
I-I don't know!

00:12:45.875 --> 00:12:50.750
Come on, hurry up! We're making it
to that lake in a single flight!

00:12:50.750 --> 00:12:51.958
Right!

00:12:55.083 --> 00:12:59.083
"World Tree
January 21, 2025"

00:13:13.375 --> 00:13:15.042
My, my...

00:13:15.458 --> 00:13:18.083
You're such a stubborn woman.

00:13:18.417 --> 00:13:22.958
It's just a fake body. I'm not
going to hurt you in any way.

00:13:22.958 --> 00:13:26.708
Don't you want
to enjoy yourself a little?

00:13:26.708 --> 00:13:28.667
You wouldn't understand.

00:13:28.667 --> 00:13:32.542
It doesn't matter whether
your body is real or virtual.

00:13:32.542 --> 00:13:34.833
Not to me anyway.

00:13:34.833 --> 00:13:38.333
You're trying to say
it'll taint your mind?

00:13:38.333 --> 00:13:42.792
I think it'd be wise to learn
to enjoy yourself while you can.

00:13:42.792 --> 00:13:45.333
I won't be here forever.

00:13:45.333 --> 00:13:48.625
I'm sure... he'll come save me.

00:13:49.000 --> 00:13:52.292
Who will?
Your boyfriend maybe?

00:13:52.625 --> 00:13:54.833
The hero Kirito.

00:13:57.250 --> 00:14:01.625
Isn't his real name Kirigaya?

00:14:02.042 --> 00:14:06.208
I met him the other day,
on the other side.

00:14:08.125 --> 00:14:14.625
I really couldn't believe that weak
little boy was the hero who beat SAO.

00:14:15.000 --> 00:14:19.917
Where do you think I met him?
Your hospital room!

00:14:19.917 --> 00:14:24.500
As you slept, I told him
I'd be marrying you next week,

00:14:24.500 --> 00:14:28.083
and the look on his face...
it was priceless.

00:14:28.083 --> 00:14:31.208
I felt like bursting into laughter.

00:14:32.667 --> 00:14:34.792
I'll bet you anything.

00:14:34.792 --> 00:14:39.125
That brat won't have the guts
to put on a NerveGear again!

00:14:41.083 --> 00:14:45.708
That's right. I have to send him
a wedding invitation.

00:14:45.708 --> 00:14:49.542
I'm sure he'll come see you
in your wedding dress.

00:14:49.542 --> 00:14:55.000
Well, I have to at least offer
our hero some crumbs like that.

00:15:00.958 --> 00:15:06.667
All right, I'll see you soon, Titania.
It'll be lonely, but you'll have to endure.

00:15:09.917 --> 00:15:11.667
<i>Kirito...</i>

00:15:12.208 --> 00:15:14.583
<i>Kirito is alive!</i>

00:15:42.417 --> 00:15:48.500
<i>8... 11... 3... 2... 9.</i>

00:15:49.083 --> 00:15:52.625
"Neutral Territory, Ancient Forest
January 21, 2025"

00:16:10.542 --> 00:16:11.750
Good work.

00:16:11.750 --> 00:16:14.417
Thanks for the backup.

00:16:16.542 --> 00:16:20.958
Our wings won't last
much longer. Let's land for a bit.

00:16:20.958 --> 00:16:22.083
Okay.

00:16:31.042 --> 00:16:33.708
--Tired?
--Nope, not yet.

00:16:33.708 --> 00:16:35.625
You hung in there.

00:16:35.625 --> 00:16:40.292
I'd like to say that, but our trip
through the sky is over for now.

00:16:40.292 --> 00:16:41.333
Why?

00:16:41.333 --> 00:16:43.583
You see that mountain, right?

00:16:43.583 --> 00:16:49.417
It's above the altitude limit, so you
have to go through caves to pass it.

00:16:49.667 --> 00:16:54.083
I've heard it's the toughest leg
between Sylph territory and Arun.

00:16:54.083 --> 00:16:56.875
I've never been past here.

00:16:56.958 --> 00:17:00.750
I see... Caves, huh? Is it long?

00:17:00.750 --> 00:17:06.083
Fairly. I hear there's a neutral mining
town midway where we can rest...

00:17:06.375 --> 00:17:09.542
Kirito, do you still have time today?

00:17:09.542 --> 00:17:13.833
It's 7:00 PM in the real world, huh?
I'm okay for a while.

00:17:13.833 --> 00:17:19.042
Okay... Then we can keep going
for a while. We can rotate out here.

00:17:19.042 --> 00:17:20.458
R-Rotate?

00:17:20.458 --> 00:17:24.458
Logging out and resting
while others keep watch.

00:17:24.458 --> 00:17:27.250
You can't log out instantly here.

00:17:27.250 --> 00:17:32.042
So you log out in turn while who's
left guards your empty avatar.

00:17:32.042 --> 00:17:35.375
I see... Got it.
You can go first.

00:17:35.375 --> 00:17:40.208
Okay, don't mind if I do.
See you in about 20 minutes.

00:18:03.250 --> 00:18:06.833
Big Brother? What should
we do for dinner?

00:18:09.125 --> 00:18:10.750
Is he asleep?

00:18:22.750 --> 00:18:25.000
"For Big Brother"

00:18:32.917 --> 00:18:36.000
<i>I'm excited.</i>

00:18:46.792 --> 00:18:48.250
<i>Kirito...</i>

00:18:49.875 --> 00:18:55.917
<i>It's not that I'm in love or anything.</i>
<i>Or that I'm glad to adventure with someone.</i>

00:18:55.917 --> 00:19:00.708
<i>I'm just looking forward</i>
<i>to journeying to a new world.</i>

00:19:12.667 --> 00:19:15.792
I'm back. See any monsters?

00:19:15.792 --> 00:19:20.167
--Welcome back. It was quiet.
--What's that?

00:19:20.167 --> 00:19:24.000
I bought some at
an item shop before we left.

00:19:24.000 --> 00:19:27.250
An NPC said
it was Sylvain's specialty.

00:19:27.250 --> 00:19:29.958
I've never heard of them.

00:19:40.625 --> 00:19:44.958
Okay, it's my turn now.
Keep me safe.

00:19:44.958 --> 00:19:47.042
Okay, bye.

00:20:02.875 --> 00:20:06.500
Y-You can move
without your master here?

00:20:06.500 --> 00:20:10.583
Of course I can!
I'm my own person.

00:20:10.583 --> 00:20:14.458
And he's not my master.
He's my daddy.

00:20:14.458 --> 00:20:18.875
Come to think of it, why do
you call Kirito your daddy?

00:20:18.875 --> 00:20:22.125
Did he, um, set it that way?

00:20:23.333 --> 00:20:25.750
He saved me.

00:20:26.042 --> 00:20:31.208
He said I was his daughter.
So he's my daddy.

00:20:31.417 --> 00:20:33.292
I-I see...

00:20:34.292 --> 00:20:36.583
Do you like him?

00:20:38.417 --> 00:20:42.583
Leafa, what does it mean
to like someone?

00:20:42.583 --> 00:20:44.792
What does it mean?

00:20:44.792 --> 00:20:50.208
You want to be with them all the time.
You get excited when you're together.

00:20:50.208 --> 00:20:52.375
Something like that?

00:20:54.833 --> 00:20:57.833
--What's wrong, Leafa?
--N-Nothing!

00:20:57.833 --> 00:20:59.625
What's nothing?

00:21:01.042 --> 00:21:03.875
I'm back.
Did something happen?

00:21:03.875 --> 00:21:09.250
Welcome back, Daddy. I was just
talking with Leafa. About what--

00:21:09.667 --> 00:21:11.625
I said it's nothing!

00:21:11.625 --> 00:21:15.792
Th-That was fast.
Did you get to eat?

00:21:15.792 --> 00:21:18.667
Yeah, my family left me something.

00:21:18.667 --> 00:21:21.958
I see... Then let's get going.

00:21:23.917 --> 00:21:27.000
Y-Yeah. Let's go then.

00:21:29.708 --> 00:21:32.375
--Is something wrong?
--Well...

00:21:32.375 --> 00:21:37.583
It felt like someone was watching us.
Yui, are any players nearby?

00:21:37.958 --> 00:21:40.875
No, I don't detect anything.

00:21:40.875 --> 00:21:43.625
There might be a tracer on us.

00:21:43.625 --> 00:21:44.958
What's that?

00:21:44.958 --> 00:21:46.750
Tracking magic.

00:21:46.750 --> 00:21:51.250
A small animal or insect
tells the caster the target's position.

00:21:51.250 --> 00:21:55.333
--Can't you get rid of it?
--You can if you find the tracer.

00:21:55.333 --> 00:21:59.875
But if the caster's magic skill
is high, it can be farther away.

00:21:59.875 --> 00:22:02.583
It'd be futile to search in this field.

00:22:02.583 --> 00:22:08.125
I see. Well, it could just be my imagination.
Anyway, let's get going.

00:22:08.125 --> 00:22:09.125
Yeah.

00:22:18.000 --> 00:22:25.083
<i>Higher and higher,</i>
<i>I reach out my arms</i>

00:22:25.083 --> 00:22:34.917
<i>"Surely, surely..."</i>
<i>I'll wish for it once again</i>

00:22:46.083 --> 00:22:53.042
<i>These endless feelings were</i>
<i>swallowed up into my daily life</i>

00:22:53.333 --> 00:23:00.125
<i>Swaying as they</i>
<i>change shape yet again</i>

00:23:00.458 --> 00:23:07.500
<i>Is it too late now? I ask</i>
<i>myself but receive no answer</i>

00:23:07.500 --> 00:23:15.000
<i>It's all up to me now,</i>
<i>both the ending and the beginning</i>

00:23:15.208 --> 00:23:22.125
<i>Higher and higher,</i>
<i>I reach out my arms</i>

00:23:22.125 --> 00:23:29.250
<i>I'm going to spread my wings</i>
<i>and head towards that gentle light</i>

00:23:29.250 --> 00:23:36.750
